WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:48.675 --> 01:50.142
[Screams]

02:37.524 --> 02:40.459
My firm's done a tremendous
amount of market research.

02:40.560 --> 02:42.152
We've discovered two things:

02:42.262 --> 02:46.756
One, most Americans feel
that Christmas is a time for family.

02:46.866 --> 02:51.098
Two, most Americans feel that in order
to stand being around their family,

02:51.204 --> 02:52.603
for even one or two days,

02:52.705 --> 02:56.732
they need to swill as much
alcohol as humanly possible.

02:56.843 --> 03:00.074
Now, I'd like you
to meet the Noggertons.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.114
They're a classic American family.

03:02.215 --> 03:04.979
They're together on Christmas,
they're fat-free,

03:05.084 --> 03:06.847
and 10 percent alcohol
by volume.

03:06.953 --> 03:11.322
Enjoy our family, so you can
enjoy your family.

03:11.424 --> 03:12.789
What do you think?

03:12.892 --> 03:17.090
So, you're suggesting we tell people
the only way to get through the holidays

03:17.197 --> 03:19.597
is to drink spiked egg nog?

03:19.699 --> 03:22.224
I'm suggesting the only way
to get through the holidays

03:22.335 --> 03:25.896
is to buy your farm-fresh, fat-free,
pre-spiked egg nog in a bottle.

03:27.974 --> 03:32.206
- Take care. All right.
- It's all good. How do you do it?

03:32.312 --> 03:34.974
I'm very excited.
I look forward to it.

03:35.081 --> 03:36.708
It went pretty well, huh?

03:36.816 --> 03:38.113
I'm a genius.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.812
I feel like I could sell
whale steaks to Greenpeace.

03:40.920 --> 03:42.251
Nice image.

03:42.355 --> 03:45.347
- Here are your tickets to Fiji.
- Ah.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.259
[Drew] Missy, we've been
dating a while.

03:56.369 --> 03:58.735
Let's take our relationship
to the next level.

03:58.838 --> 04:00.806
[Missy] I've hoped you would say that.

04:00.907 --> 04:03.535
[Drew] I got you a little
pre-Christmas Christmas gift.

04:03.643 --> 04:05.304
[Missy] Yeah?

04:05.411 --> 04:10.405
I want you to open it now
because it involves our future.

04:10.516 --> 04:13.679
The future of you and me together.

04:13.786 --> 04:16.687
It's kind of for both of us,
in that way.

04:18.658 --> 04:20.750
[Gasps]

04:20.860 --> 04:22.487
[Breathless] Okay.

04:29.969 --> 04:31.436
Tickets to Fiji?

04:31.537 --> 04:33.869
Yes. First class.

04:33.973 --> 04:35.531
Drew, on Christmas?

04:35.642 --> 04:38.338
Christmas is the family holiday.

04:38.444 --> 04:42.346
I mean, what are we doing? What is this?
I mean, what is going on?

04:42.448 --> 04:44.882
Where is this relationship headed?

04:45.918 --> 04:48.546
Fiji. First class.

04:48.655 --> 04:52.284
- Missy?
- Uh-uh. Okay.

04:52.392 --> 04:54.553
Here's an example
of one of our problems.

04:54.661 --> 04:58.495
You never introduced me to your family.
You never mentioned your family.

04:58.598 --> 04:59.963
Do you even have a family?

05:00.066 --> 05:04.526
How can you be serious about me,
if you're not serious about your family?

05:04.637 --> 05:07.197
You need to get some
serious help, Drew.

05:07.307 --> 05:09.172
I think you're missing the point.

05:09.275 --> 05:13.075
If I told you everything about me,
there'd be no more sense of mystery.

05:13.179 --> 05:14.578
Nothing left to discover.

05:14.681 --> 05:17.377
With nothing left to discover,
a relationship dies.

05:17.483 --> 05:19.781
You don't want this to die, do you?

05:19.886 --> 05:22.286
It just did.

05:24.424 --> 05:27.120
Come on. Don't be like that.

05:27.226 --> 05:29.524
You're gonna be like that?
Go ahead. Go.

05:29.629 --> 05:32.029
I'm going to spend Christmas
with my family.

05:32.131 --> 05:34.122
You can spend Christmas alone.

05:37.737 --> 05:39.329
[Drew] Missy.

05:58.591 --> 06:03.858
Kathryn, I need you to get
a Cartier bracelet to send to Missy.

06:03.963 --> 06:06.955
Something expensive,
a lot of diamonds, very flashy.

06:07.066 --> 06:10.695
- Include a personal note from me.
- What exactly do you want it to say?

06:10.803 --> 06:14.534
Something personal that shows
the depth of my feelings, my emotions.

06:14.640 --> 06:18.701
- You're good. That's why I hired you.
- Okay, but it's not gonna work.

06:22.749 --> 06:24.410
My man.

06:27.253 --> 06:29.278
Oh, Dougie!

06:29.389 --> 06:31.380
Doogan. Doog-ray.

06:31.491 --> 06:33.322
Douglas.

06:33.426 --> 06:35.326
It's Drew.

06:35.428 --> 06:37.191
Drew Latham.
[Chuckles]

06:37.296 --> 06:39.025
Yeah. What's up, man?

06:39.132 --> 06:41.930
What are you up?
Ah, nothin', nothin'.

06:42.034 --> 06:45.265
Hey, man,
what're you doing for Christmas?

06:45.371 --> 06:48.465
Family? Nice. Nice call.

06:48.574 --> 06:51.304
Uh, you got room for one more?

06:52.345 --> 06:55.576
Well, I think we are that close.

06:57.683 --> 07:01.483
I love Jewish Christ...
I'll light candles, spin the dreidel.

07:01.587 --> 07:05.114
It'll be great,
a matzo ball soup and baklava.

07:05.224 --> 07:08.887
All right, well, that's Greek.
Fine, whatever. I'm just...

07:08.995 --> 07:10.121
You still there?

07:11.631 --> 07:14.532
I know you have a baby.
I'm just saying, like, you know,

07:14.634 --> 07:17.899
they just lie there
and crap themselves, right?

07:18.004 --> 07:20.472
After a while,
how interesting is that?

07:20.573 --> 07:23.565
No, I'm not saying anything bad.
I'm just sayin'...

07:23.676 --> 07:25.405
Huh?

07:25.511 --> 07:28.275
Well, maybe, your wife
doesn't have to come, man.

07:28.381 --> 07:30.349
Maybe it's me and you
for Christmas.

07:30.450 --> 07:31.974
You ever think about that?

07:34.921 --> 07:38.857
Would you mind if I came by
to your house and spent Christmas?

07:38.958 --> 07:43.054
It's like one or two, three days, tops.

07:43.162 --> 07:45.323
[Pen scratching]

08:33.145 --> 08:35.578
[Sighs] All right.

08:35.681 --> 08:38.275
Merry Christmas.

08:41.354 --> 08:43.686
[Jet engines roaring]

08:44.924 --> 08:47.654
[Man] Okay, right over here.
Everybody stay together.

08:47.760 --> 08:50.456
All real good.
Okay, you've got Tu-Tu...

08:50.563 --> 08:53.532
[Drew] Doctor Freeman!
Thank God, I found you.

08:53.633 --> 08:55.123
[Freeman] Sir, sir...

08:55.234 --> 08:58.601
I gotta spend Christmas alone.
I'm having a panic attack.

08:58.704 --> 09:01.832
- You gotta help me. Please!
- Who are you? I don't know you.

09:01.941 --> 09:04.171
I'm the boyfriend
of one of your patients.

09:04.277 --> 09:05.904
- You are?
- Missy Vangilder.

09:06.012 --> 09:08.776
[Laughing] You're Drew.
You're Drew. Oh, God.

09:08.881 --> 09:11.372
- What does that mean?
- I'm not allowed to say.

09:11.484 --> 09:14.214
- How did you find me?
- I bribed a woman at your service.

09:14.320 --> 09:17.721
She should raise her standards
or you gotta fire her.

09:17.823 --> 09:19.518
She totally caved for 200 bucks.

09:19.625 --> 09:21.490
- Whatever.
- I need a few minutes.

09:21.594 --> 09:23.960
[Freeman] Backpacks on the belt.
Game Boy too.

09:24.063 --> 09:27.294
You gotta help me out.
I don't wanna spend Christmas alone.

09:27.400 --> 09:28.628
If you would just please!

09:28.734 --> 09:30.634
She's gotta put
the bear on the belt.

09:30.736 --> 09:32.226
Can't she walk it through?

09:32.338 --> 09:34.067
She's got to put it on the belt.

09:34.173 --> 09:36.164
- It's a puppy!
- I know it's a puppy.

09:36.275 --> 09:38.175
Put Tu-Tu on
and she'll go for a ride.

09:38.277 --> 09:40.609
- My Tu-Tu!
- I need one second.

09:40.713 --> 09:41.975
If you could just please!

09:42.081 --> 09:45.517
- Okay, gimme the puppy.
- Sir, I need you to step here.

09:45.618 --> 09:50.214
- [Drew] You're abusing your child.
- Can you see I've got my own problems?

09:50.323 --> 09:53.258
- Whoa, whoa, now.
- I'm sorry. I am so sorry.

09:53.359 --> 09:57.420
Okay. Okay.
Hey, I know.

09:57.530 --> 09:59.794
- Heard it on the radio once.
- All right.

09:59.899 --> 10:02.834
Write down your grievances
about your family on paper.

10:02.935 --> 10:04.596
- All your grievances.
- Right.

10:04.704 --> 10:07.502
Go someplace that reminds you
of your childhood,

10:07.607 --> 10:10.167
at sunset and light
that piece of paper on fire.

10:10.276 --> 10:13.871
As the last shred of paper
is burning away, you whisper,

10:13.980 --> 10:15.208
"I forgive you."

10:15.314 --> 10:17.282
- "I forgive you."
- Mm-hm.

10:17.383 --> 10:19.578
- And it burns up.
- That's it.

10:19.685 --> 10:20.879
I like it.

10:20.987 --> 10:22.955
- Oh, thanks so much!
- Whoa! All right.

10:23.055 --> 10:25.683
- Have a good vaca.
- Where's my daughter?

10:25.791 --> 10:26.883
- [Beeping]
- Sir?

10:26.993 --> 10:28.517
Huh? Oh, there she is.

10:28.628 --> 10:31.461
Whoa! Hey! Come on out!
Come out for Daddy!

10:44.377 --> 10:46.777
My grievances.

11:02.361 --> 11:04.989
Okay, buddy, here we go.
That'll be $ 72.50.

11:05.097 --> 11:06.792
My God!

11:06.899 --> 11:08.594
That's it!

11:08.701 --> 11:10.669
That's the house I grew up in.

11:10.770 --> 11:13.830
How's the $ 72.50 comin'?

11:13.939 --> 11:16.931
Good. It's comin' good.

11:17.043 --> 11:18.908
Keep the meter running.

11:41.634 --> 11:44.603
- [Tom] Almost out of salami.
- [Christine] No.

11:44.704 --> 11:46.331
Well, thank you for telling me.

11:46.439 --> 11:49.135
- I don't wanna run out, that's all.
- God forbid.

11:49.241 --> 11:51.175
- Did Brian eat?
- I don't know.

11:51.277 --> 11:53.711
[Shouting] Get down here
and eat your dinner.

11:53.813 --> 11:56.475
- I'm not hungry!
- [Tom] Yeah, you are!

11:56.582 --> 11:59.278
[Christine] Stop yelling at me.

11:59.385 --> 12:00.943
[Tom] I'm not yelling at you.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.212
Brian!

12:06.525 --> 12:07.992
[Shouting] Brian!

12:08.094 --> 12:12.155
Get down here please, so your father
can stop not yelling at me!

12:12.264 --> 12:14.129
I'm busy!

12:14.233 --> 12:16.463
We shouldn't have put
the computer in his room.

12:16.569 --> 12:18.469
He's gonna spend
all his time there.

12:18.571 --> 12:20.869
Oh, Tom.
Welcome to the future, dear.

12:20.973 --> 12:22.440
He's advancing his skills.

12:22.541 --> 12:25.669
One day that computer's
gonna get our baby a good job.

12:25.778 --> 12:27.769
[Beeping]

12:27.880 --> 12:30.440
[Music plays, woman's voice]

12:32.752 --> 12:35.448
Trust me. What he's doin',
nobody's gonna pay for,

12:35.554 --> 12:38.352
'cause if they did,
I'd have retired at 17.

12:42.528 --> 12:45.520
- [Tom] What?
- There's a guy out there.

12:45.631 --> 12:47.565
Who the hell is that?

12:59.178 --> 13:01.942
[Drew] All right. Alone on Christmas.
I can do this.

13:02.047 --> 13:07.508
[Sighs] I rid myself
of all my grievances.

13:07.620 --> 13:09.747
Be gone, grievances.

13:13.459 --> 13:14.687
What the...

13:16.996 --> 13:18.156
I forgive you.

13:21.534 --> 13:24.401
Holy Moly. This joker.

13:24.503 --> 13:26.266
[Tires screeching]

13:48.060 --> 13:50.722
What are the neighbors gonna think?

13:50.830 --> 13:54.391
Unless they want to get hit, they
shouldn't be burning crap in my yard.

13:54.500 --> 13:56.195
Is he still breathing?

13:58.204 --> 14:00.468
Dear God, Tom.
You've killed the man.

14:00.573 --> 14:02.598
Oh, shit! He's still alive!

14:02.708 --> 14:05.677
[Groaning] Hello.

14:07.146 --> 14:08.272
[Whimpers]

14:10.883 --> 14:14.250
My name is Drew Latham.
[Chuckles]

14:15.621 --> 14:18.089
I grew up in this house.

14:18.190 --> 14:21.318
That's why you came back and
tried to burn it down, Pyroboy?

14:21.427 --> 14:23.486
- Brian, call the cops.
- Oh, no, no, no!

14:23.596 --> 14:27.191
That won't be necessary. That's fine.
I was just outside burning,

14:27.299 --> 14:29.824
someone told me to burn
a list of my grievances

14:29.935 --> 14:33.393
outside of the home of my birth
to help me with loneliness issues.

14:33.505 --> 14:35.871
- So, it's all fine.
- Oh.

14:35.975 --> 14:39.934
Any-hoo, apologies
and I'm gonna go.

14:40.045 --> 14:43.378
Would you mind terribly
if I took a look-see around the house?

14:43.482 --> 14:45.882
- I'll give you a tour.
- [Drew] Oh, thank you.

14:45.985 --> 14:48.385
Hold on.

14:48.487 --> 14:51.149
- You got any more matches?
- No. No, no, no.

14:51.257 --> 14:52.656
Are we done with all that?

14:52.758 --> 14:54.123
Yes. The burning. Yes.

14:54.226 --> 14:56.786
It's completely done.
I'm actually better.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.261
I'm watching you.

15:01.333 --> 15:04.666
Wow. I can't believe it!

15:04.770 --> 15:07.398
This is amazing!
It's exactly how I remember it.

15:07.506 --> 15:11.875
- You mean it was always a shithole?
- No. No, it's great.

15:17.850 --> 15:19.511
[Squeak]

15:19.618 --> 15:22.485
- Did you hear that?
- [Squeaking]

15:22.588 --> 15:24.886
That stair squeaked.

15:24.990 --> 15:27.652
Do you know what we
used to call that squeaky stair?

15:27.760 --> 15:30.820
"The squeaky stair."
[Laughing]

15:30.930 --> 15:34.127
- [Squeaking]
- [Laughing]

15:42.541 --> 15:46.272
Wow. My old room.

15:46.378 --> 15:47.777
My God.

15:47.880 --> 15:51.077
Hey, look at that!
I can touch the ceiling.

15:51.183 --> 15:54.550
It's much smaller than I remember it.
Did you do something?

15:54.653 --> 15:57.349
Yeah. We had it reduced.

15:57.456 --> 16:00.914
Cost a lot, but yeah,
I think it was...

16:01.026 --> 16:02.459
I think it was worth it.

16:02.561 --> 16:04.756
Man, this is great.
Man, this is the best.

16:04.863 --> 16:08.299
You guys sittin' around
eatin' dinner like a family.

16:08.400 --> 16:11.335
I always wanted that.
This is really wonderful.

16:13.005 --> 16:14.233
[Brian] Wonderful.

16:14.340 --> 16:16.467
So, what's for dessert?

16:16.575 --> 16:19.203
- Kitchen's closed.
- Aw.

16:19.311 --> 16:21.302
- Yeah, I got things to do.
- Ah, boy.

16:21.413 --> 16:23.779
Tom, why don't you
see the man out?

16:23.882 --> 16:26.476
I didn't want to let him in.
I'll call you a cab.

16:26.585 --> 16:28.519
Is that necessary?

16:28.620 --> 16:29.882
Yeah, it is. Yeah.

16:29.989 --> 16:32.514
But you know, man,
I gotta tell ya,

16:32.624 --> 16:35.149
all these years I've been
avoiding Christmas,

16:35.260 --> 16:39.458
and I just realized,
this is what I've been longing for.

16:39.565 --> 16:42.830
A real family, you know?
In a true home.

16:42.935 --> 16:45.563
That's why I'm thinking

16:45.671 --> 16:48.572
it might be a good idea
if I lived with you.

16:48.674 --> 16:50.801
- [Drew grunts]
- [Door slams]

17:22.974 --> 17:25.671
[Drew knocking] Tom! Tom!

17:27.079 --> 17:29.445
Tom, please!
Please let me stay here!

17:29.548 --> 17:30.515
No.

17:30.616 --> 17:33.517
- I'll pay you.
- My family's not for sale, pal.

17:33.619 --> 17:36.315
Tom, I'll pay you $250,000.

17:37.556 --> 17:39.615
Welcome home, son.

17:40.225 --> 17:42.193
[Splashing]

17:42.294 --> 17:43.818
Mom.

17:49.301 --> 17:51.531
Tom, that guy is still here.

17:51.637 --> 17:54.401
- Yeah, I know.
- Why is he still here?

17:56.208 --> 17:59.803
He's givin' us $250,000
to be his family for Christmas.

17:59.912 --> 18:03.143
And you agreed to this?
Without asking me?

18:03.248 --> 18:06.877
Of course I did.
He's giving us $250,000.

18:06.985 --> 18:10.045
How would you like it if I
agreed to this without asking you?

18:10.155 --> 18:13.124
Well, that would depend.
Would we be getting $250,000?

18:16.361 --> 18:18.955
Okay. What exactly
did you agree to?

18:22.000 --> 18:23.262
[Sighs]

18:30.342 --> 18:32.207
It's a big day for this family.

18:32.311 --> 18:34.142
- Very well.
- All right.

18:34.246 --> 18:38.114
Mr. Latham agrees
to pay the sum of $250,000

18:38.217 --> 18:43.746
to the Valcos for services rendered
until 11:59 pm on Christmas Day.

18:43.856 --> 18:46.620
And for said sum, the Valco family

18:46.725 --> 18:50.024
will aid Mr. Latham in recapturing

18:50.129 --> 18:53.189
those childhood Christmas memories,

18:53.298 --> 18:55.960
- including, but not limited to,
- [sighs]

18:56.068 --> 19:00.664
All due festiveness, celebrations,
various and sundry merriments,

19:00.772 --> 19:02.865
and yuletide glee.

19:02.975 --> 19:05.034
Agreed!

19:05.144 --> 19:07.044
Agreed, right?

19:07.146 --> 19:09.376
Fakin' it anyway.
Might as well get paid.

19:09.481 --> 19:11.244
Will there be anything else?

19:11.350 --> 19:13.545
Oh, yeah. I gotta sleep
in Brian's room.

19:13.652 --> 19:16.644
What? No.
Where is this going here?

19:16.755 --> 19:19.952
Like it says in the contract.
I get to sleep in my old room.

19:20.058 --> 19:23.960
Oh, come on. Creepy grievance guy
wants to sleep in my room?

19:24.062 --> 19:27.930
If I wanted that, I'd use a bus ticket
those guys send me on the Internet.

19:28.033 --> 19:30.968
I just wanna sleep in my room,
like it says in the contract.

19:31.069 --> 19:33.162
Brian, you're in the guest room.

19:33.272 --> 19:37.333
My computer's not in the guest room.
How am I supposed to... study?

19:37.442 --> 19:39.307
Use your imagination.

19:39.411 --> 19:42.107
Well, I'm gonna
catch some shut-eye.

19:42.214 --> 19:46.275
Who wants to go Christmas tree
shopping with me in the morning?

19:49.121 --> 19:51.646
Apparently, you all do.

19:51.757 --> 19:51.857
[Birds chirping]

19:51.857 --> 19:54.018
[Birds chirping]

19:57.896 --> 19:59.761
[Yawns]

20:12.244 --> 20:14.041
I'm home.

20:27.259 --> 20:29.056
Oh!

20:30.128 --> 20:32.153
[Christine] Brian? Brian!

20:32.264 --> 20:34.095
[Brian] I didn't do it.

20:34.199 --> 20:35.393
[Drew] It's all right.

20:35.500 --> 20:39.334
[Chuckling] I'll fix it.
I'll fix it. Ow.

20:46.178 --> 20:49.079
[Tom] Well, that should do it,
assuming no other idiot...

20:55.787 --> 20:57.152
Is he eatin' my salami?

20:57.256 --> 20:59.383
That's what it looks like.

21:01.293 --> 21:05.627
- It's 9:00 in the mornin'.
- Oh, I know. It's not breakfast food,

21:05.731 --> 21:08.063
but it was lookin' good.
I had to dog some.

21:08.166 --> 21:10.726
Yeah, it is good.

21:10.836 --> 21:13.964
- Is that the last of it?
- Yep.

21:26.051 --> 21:29.043
Oh. You didn't want some, did ya?

21:29.154 --> 21:31.816
No. It's all right.
It's fine, it's fine.

21:31.923 --> 21:33.413
Ah.

21:35.994 --> 21:38.394
[Drew] Kathryn, I hope
you're checking messages.

21:38.497 --> 21:41.159
Should anyone need to reach me,
they can call my cell.

21:41.266 --> 21:42.790
If you need to send anything,

21:42.901 --> 21:47.463
the address is 2 Edgewood Road
in Lincoln Wood, Illinois.

21:47.572 --> 21:49.506
Stayin' with my family.

21:50.776 --> 21:51.902
Hey, Dad?

21:54.813 --> 21:57.145
He's talkin' to you, genius.

21:58.617 --> 22:00.517
Yeah, Drew?

22:02.120 --> 22:06.113
Would you do me a kindness?
Put this hat on.

22:06.224 --> 22:09.455
My dad used to wear a Santa hat
when we went Christmas tree shopping.

22:09.561 --> 22:10.585
[Laughter]

22:10.696 --> 22:12.493
- In public?
- Yeah.

22:12.597 --> 22:14.121
That would be no.

22:14.232 --> 22:17.463
And in private,
that would be no, too.

22:17.569 --> 22:19.196
Please wear the hat.

22:20.372 --> 22:22.567
No. I'm not wearing the hat.

22:22.674 --> 22:24.801
Tom, you gotta wear the hat.

22:24.910 --> 22:27.310
- I'm not wearin' the hat.
- Wear the hat, Tom.

22:27.412 --> 22:30.176
Now get it away from me
before I shove it up your ass.

22:32.651 --> 22:36.212
Tom, are you familiar
with the phrase "breach of contract?"

22:40.926 --> 22:44.362
- Give me the hat.
- All right.

22:44.463 --> 22:48.797
$250,000. $250,000.

22:48.900 --> 22:52.028
- $250,000.
- [Brian chuckling]

22:52.137 --> 22:53.570
You're lookin' good, Dad.

22:53.672 --> 22:55.435
- [Christine] Tom!
- Shut up!

22:55.540 --> 22:57.371
Eyes on the road.
On the road. Dad.

22:57.476 --> 22:59.034
- Gimme your leg.
- [Screeching]

22:59.211 --> 23:01.076
[Drew] No.

23:04.883 --> 23:06.680
Nope.

23:06.785 --> 23:08.480
Oh, wait a minute.

23:08.587 --> 23:10.487
This could be it.
This could be it.

23:10.589 --> 23:12.887
Yep. This is it.
This is the one.

23:12.991 --> 23:15.221
[Drew] You're good.
Excuse me, folks.

23:16.228 --> 23:21.131
Dad, you wanna lift that up,
have respect for the tree? No?

23:21.233 --> 23:23.861
It's gonna be in our house, so...

23:23.969 --> 23:26.665
Wait, wait, wait.
Where are we going with this?

23:28.173 --> 23:31.233
All right. Let's get that baby up there,
hoist that up.

23:31.343 --> 23:33.777
- Get that on the roof.
- [Tom grunts]

23:33.879 --> 23:35.608
All righty.

23:35.714 --> 23:37.616
[Drew] That's pretty good. All right!
You got it. There you go.

23:37.616 --> 23:39.277
[Drew] That's pretty good. All right!
You got it. There you go.

23:39.384 --> 23:41.249
Get around it.
Get around on it.

23:41.353 --> 23:42.547
[Tom straining]

23:42.654 --> 23:46.055
Brian, get your skinny little ass
out of the car!

23:46.158 --> 23:47.921
[Drew] You got it, Dad.
You got it.

23:48.026 --> 23:49.550
You got it.

23:49.661 --> 23:53.324
Nice one. All right, I think it's good.
I think it's good like that.

23:53.432 --> 23:56.401
Whoo! Christmas time.

24:01.473 --> 24:04.909
- [Drew] How's it look?
- [Brian] It could trigger a seizure.

24:05.010 --> 24:07.535
I know.
Wait till you see it lit up.

24:07.646 --> 24:08.943
I thought it was lit up.

24:09.047 --> 24:10.173
Oh no, no, no.

24:10.282 --> 24:13.809
<i>We gotta sing Christmas Tree first.
Tom, you take the lead.</i>

24:14.653 --> 24:17.451
- You want me to sing?
- Yeah.

24:18.557 --> 24:20.616
Do I have to?

24:20.725 --> 24:22.022
Yeah.

24:22.761 --> 24:25.286
Would it make any difference
if I didn't want to?

24:25.397 --> 24:26.489
Not really.

24:28.900 --> 24:30.731
Come on.

24:32.771 --> 24:34.796
<i>Oh, Christmas tree</i>

24:34.906 --> 24:37.374
Christine, you wanna
help me out here a little?

24:37.476 --> 24:39.444
No, you're doin' great.

24:39.544 --> 24:43.503
You're doin' good, Dad.
Come on. You can do it.

24:46.918 --> 24:50.718
<i>[Both] Oh, Christmas tree
Oh, Christmas tree</i>

24:50.822 --> 24:54.258
<i>You stand in woodland beauty</i>

24:54.359 --> 24:56.156
<i>You are as green</i>

24:56.261 --> 24:58.092
<i>- As winter snow
- As summer snow</i>

24:58.196 --> 25:00.460
<i>- Winter snow.
- Winter snow</i>

25:00.565 --> 25:04.092
<i>As in summer's brightest glow</i>

25:04.202 --> 25:09.435
<i>Oh, Christmas tree
Oh, Christmas tree</i>

25:09.541 --> 25:14.706
<i>You stand in woodland beauty</i>

25:14.813 --> 25:16.508
<i>Ahhh</i>

25:16.615 --> 25:17.843
That was great.

25:17.949 --> 25:20.440
- [Drew] That was good.
- [Tom] That was, yeah.

25:20.552 --> 25:21.519
All right.

25:21.620 --> 25:26.421
Without further ado, let's fire it up.
Ready? One, two...

25:26.525 --> 25:28.755
- [knocking]
- [Groans]

25:28.860 --> 25:31.260
All right, people.
Take five. I'll deal with this.

25:31.363 --> 25:33.194
Thank Christ.

25:34.799 --> 25:36.164
Can I help you?

25:38.303 --> 25:40.794
Yeah. Who are you?

25:40.906 --> 25:42.533
Um, who are you?

25:42.641 --> 25:44.336
[Christine] Alicia!

25:44.442 --> 25:46.672
Hey, Mom. Hi. Who's this?

25:46.778 --> 25:48.973
Mom, who is this?

25:49.080 --> 25:50.775
Okay, what's going on?

25:50.882 --> 25:54.147
Dad's rented us for the holidays
to this eccentric millionaire.

25:54.252 --> 25:57.619
[Drew] You have a daughter?
Since when do you have a daughter?

25:57.722 --> 26:00.987
- It's her terrible secret.
- This is gonna ruin everything.

26:01.092 --> 26:03.560
- The whole bit doesn't work.
- Ruin? Know what?

26:03.662 --> 26:07.530
Shh. Will somebody say something
that makes some sense right now?

26:07.632 --> 26:09.896
Well, around Christmas,
I get anxiety...

26:10.001 --> 26:12.333
No, no. You stop talking. Mom?

26:12.437 --> 26:15.634
Drew wants a family Christmas,
so we're gonna be his family.

26:15.740 --> 26:17.503
- That's insane.
- Tell me about it.

26:17.609 --> 26:20.339
I never had a sister,
so this is bullshit right here.

26:20.445 --> 26:22.970
Okay. You are my
illegitimate love child.

26:23.081 --> 26:25.447
- Mom!
- And you had no idea about her.

26:25.550 --> 26:27.450
That could be good.
You know what?

26:27.552 --> 26:29.850
- She could be the maid!
- Okay. Enough.

26:29.955 --> 26:31.684
Hey, my baby's home.

26:31.790 --> 26:33.621
- Hi, Daddy.
- How are you, Lissi?

26:33.725 --> 26:36.990
Hi. I'm good.
You've obviously lost your mind.

26:37.095 --> 26:39.620
Can I talk to you
in the dining room, please?

26:39.731 --> 26:40.857
You knew about this?

26:40.966 --> 26:43.457
- Stay away from my daughter.
- Okay, Mom?

26:43.568 --> 26:45.593
- This guy is obviously crazy.
- I know.

26:45.704 --> 26:48.002
So, I'm gonna go upstairs,
and take a bath,

26:48.106 --> 26:51.371
and when I wake up in the morning,
he's gonna be gone, right?

26:51.476 --> 26:52.704
Maybe.

26:52.811 --> 26:55.439
I'm not gonna be a good sport
about this, Mom.

26:55.547 --> 26:58.015
Oh, darling, we'd never
expect you to be.

26:59.551 --> 27:01.109
Thanks.

27:01.219 --> 27:03.779
[Drew] Come on, Mom!
It's tree time!

27:08.560 --> 27:09.754
[Drew] Okey-dokey.

27:09.861 --> 27:12.227
All right.
We're back on track.

27:16.401 --> 27:17.663
Yeah.

27:18.803 --> 27:20.964
Okay.

27:21.072 --> 27:25.236
Here we go.
One, two, three!

27:27.812 --> 27:30.303
[Drew] Now it feels like Christmas.

27:30.415 --> 27:32.883
[Brian] I can smell
my eyeballs burning.

27:32.984 --> 27:35.976
[Drew] Very important.
Don't look directly at the tree.

27:36.154 --> 27:37.712
[Dog barking]

27:45.930 --> 27:47.261
- Brian!
- What?

27:47.365 --> 27:49.299
Wake up!
It's your brother, kind of!

27:49.401 --> 27:51.699
It's snowing outside!
It's a snow day!

27:53.071 --> 27:54.504
Why are you waking me up?

27:54.606 --> 27:56.972
I don't want you
to miss the fun, man!

27:58.410 --> 28:00.002
What fun?

28:00.111 --> 28:04.309
[Drew] Oh! Facial! Iceball!
Whoo! Ha ha!

28:04.416 --> 28:06.441
Look out! Oh!

28:06.551 --> 28:08.212
Right in the nuts!
In the nuts!

28:08.319 --> 28:10.287
- I can't feel my toes.
- Here he comes.

28:10.388 --> 28:13.482
The look of vengeance.
Eye of the tiger.

28:13.591 --> 28:15.456
Oh, oh.
Now he's getting furious.

28:15.560 --> 28:17.391
Whoo! Whoo!

28:18.530 --> 28:20.930
- Whoo!
- [Door closing]

28:23.601 --> 28:26.661
- What's up, Tom?
- Brian, go inside.

28:27.706 --> 28:30.504
See you later, Bri.
It was fun.

28:30.608 --> 28:32.473
You like throwing snowballs?

28:32.577 --> 28:34.841
I was just havin' a good time.
You know.

28:34.946 --> 28:37.141
Yeah. Throw one at me.

28:37.248 --> 28:39.512
That's cool.
Don't worry about it.

28:39.617 --> 28:41.141
We're kinda finished now.

28:41.252 --> 28:43.379
Come on.
Like you said, it'll be fun.

28:43.488 --> 28:46.286
It's getting a little chilly.
I don't wanna bother.

28:46.391 --> 28:49.224
- Don't worry about it.
- Ah, come on. Throw it.

28:50.762 --> 28:52.992
All right, I'll throw one,
I'll throw one.

28:59.537 --> 29:01.402
Good one.

29:03.074 --> 29:04.439
Now it's my turn.

29:06.878 --> 29:08.709
No!

29:11.883 --> 29:13.475
That was great.

29:13.585 --> 29:15.746
Any time you wanna do that,
let me know.

29:15.854 --> 29:17.754
We said no iceballs, man.

29:17.856 --> 29:19.619
Oh, did we?

29:20.859 --> 29:22.292
Morning, Mom.

29:22.393 --> 29:24.020
Freak.

29:25.764 --> 29:26.856
You know what?

29:28.600 --> 29:31.228
We may have gotten off
on the wrong track.

29:31.336 --> 29:32.633
We should start over.

29:32.737 --> 29:34.568
- Here you go, Drew.
- Thanks, Mom.

29:34.672 --> 29:36.572
- Mmm.
- Problem?

29:36.674 --> 29:40.201
My real mom puts marshmallows
in the hot chocolate.

29:40.311 --> 29:43.405
Know what I was thinking?
If you don't wanna play my sister,

29:43.515 --> 29:46.507
maybe you could be, like,
a wonderful, mysterious

29:46.618 --> 29:49.416
Ecuadorean cleaning lady.
You know?

29:49.521 --> 29:52.388
Or Swedish cleaning lady.
The ethnicity's not important.

29:52.490 --> 29:55.084
But cleaning lady's good.
Oh. Mmm.

29:55.193 --> 29:56.660
What?

29:56.761 --> 29:59.821
My real mom used the
mini-marshmallows. Sorry.

29:59.931 --> 30:04.527
Speaking of your mom, why aren't you
annoying your own family?

30:04.636 --> 30:07.605
That's not really your business,
is it, Consuela?

30:14.412 --> 30:16.573
[Drew] Ho, ho, ho!

30:16.681 --> 30:19.912
All righty.
Welcome, everyone.

30:21.653 --> 30:23.382
- Here you are.
- What is this?

30:23.488 --> 30:26.980
These are what we
in the business call scripts, Tom.

30:27.091 --> 30:29.821
- Excuse me?
- You don't have to worry about it.

30:29.928 --> 30:31.953
Your role is what we call "small."

30:32.063 --> 30:35.692
Well, you're what we
in real life call "a jackass."

30:35.800 --> 30:38.769
I don't know about that,
but I do know that my being here

30:38.870 --> 30:41.839
may have caused some awkwardness
within the family.

30:41.940 --> 30:44.408
- You think?
- [Drew] I do, Tom. Seriously.

30:44.509 --> 30:48.104
And it's even possible
that some of it could potentially be

30:48.213 --> 30:50.443
in some small way
partly my fault.

30:50.548 --> 30:52.914
Which part wasn't your fault?

30:53.017 --> 30:55.451
Bop, bop, bop, bop.
I'm talking. Okay?

30:55.553 --> 30:58.818
So what I've done is I went
ahead and wrote a sequence,

30:58.923 --> 31:02.051
so you guys can get a sense
of what I'm going for here.

31:02.160 --> 31:04.062
And we're all gonna
read this aloud.

31:04.062 --> 31:04.721
And we're all gonna
read this aloud.

31:04.829 --> 31:08.128
- I feel like I'm insane.
- That's why you have no lines.

31:08.233 --> 31:10.861
- Mom, I believe you go first.
- Okay.

31:10.969 --> 31:12.834
"Oh, look at us.

31:12.937 --> 31:16.771
I sure hope you like the meal
I so lovingly prepared

31:16.875 --> 31:18.809
for the people I love.

31:18.910 --> 31:22.209
She smiles at Tom."
Oh, she's...

31:23.081 --> 31:25.845
[Drew] Have you acted?
You've acted before.

31:25.950 --> 31:27.713
- A little theater.
- I can tell.

31:27.819 --> 31:31.277
<i>- I see it. It comes out.
- You were in Pippin in high school.</i>

31:31.389 --> 31:33.880
You played Wind.

31:33.992 --> 31:36.324
Tom, you have the next line.

31:36.427 --> 31:38.122
Uh...

31:38.229 --> 31:41.630
"Say thank you to your mother
for all her hard work cooking for us."

31:41.733 --> 31:44.065
"Thank you."

31:44.168 --> 31:46.636
"Oh, I don't work nearly
as hard as you, dear."

31:46.738 --> 31:48.000
Well, that's true.

31:48.106 --> 31:51.132
Tom, let's stay on book, please.
Brian, go ahead.

31:51.242 --> 31:54.905
"Gee, Mom, I love you
like the dickens.

31:55.013 --> 31:56.981
Should we pray?"

31:57.081 --> 32:00.448
Gee, Beav, do you think Wally's
gonna give you the business?

32:00.551 --> 32:03.019
Oh, there you are, Consuela.

32:03.121 --> 32:06.750
<i>Five waters for everyone, please.
Gracias.</i>

32:06.858 --> 32:09.952
[Clears throat] Brian,
you were about to say grace.

32:11.663 --> 32:15.497
- "Dear God..."
- Brian. We hold hands at grace.

32:18.536 --> 32:20.527
[Brian] "Dear God,

32:20.638 --> 32:22.003
thank you for this meal.

32:22.106 --> 32:24.131
Thank you for blessing us
with a family.

32:24.242 --> 32:25.869
Not everyone has a nice family.

32:25.977 --> 32:27.638
And also we, O Lord,

32:27.745 --> 32:31.078
are so lucky to have Drew
in our lives."

32:31.182 --> 32:32.877
Amen.

32:34.285 --> 32:36.515
"An emotional moment."

32:36.621 --> 32:38.486
Sorry, I keep doing that.

32:38.589 --> 32:42.081
"Brian, if you eat it all up,
I will let you sleep with me

32:42.193 --> 32:45.321
like I never did
when you were little."

32:47.665 --> 32:49.963
An awkward moment.

32:50.068 --> 32:51.968
Skip ahead.
That doesn't work.

32:52.070 --> 32:54.971
- That's not supposed to be there.
- What does this mean?

32:55.073 --> 32:57.064
"Doo-Dah enters
in his bathrobe."

32:57.175 --> 33:01.111
Sweet Jim Jiminy!
Cold corn in the mornin'!

33:01.212 --> 33:05.706
- This weather is killin' my joints.
- Brian, go get the shovel.

33:05.817 --> 33:09.617
[Drew] Listen to me. When Alicia came,
she totally ruined everything.

33:09.721 --> 33:12.155
Everything was so normal
up until that point.

33:12.256 --> 33:13.587
<i>Silencio, por favor.</i>

33:13.691 --> 33:16.956
So I realized what I had to do
was expand the family.

33:17.061 --> 33:19.825
I had to find my grandpa.
So I went and found my Doo-Dah.

33:19.931 --> 33:22.092
Here he is. My Doo-Dah.

33:22.200 --> 33:25.863
<i>Your Doo-Dah looks exactly like the guy
in Christmas Carol. Scrooge.</i>

33:25.970 --> 33:28.234
That's right.
I do community theater.

33:28.339 --> 33:31.331
And this Christmas night,
I'm reprising my role as Scrooge

33:31.442 --> 33:34.036
in the Lincoln Wood
Theater Group's production

33:34.145 --> 33:36.875
<i>of A Christmas Carol.
I hope you all can make it.</i>

33:36.981 --> 33:39.506
Please stay in character, Saul, okay?

33:39.617 --> 33:41.380
"I'm so glad that you came here.

33:41.486 --> 33:44.182
You're gonna stay for
the whole Christmas holiday."

33:44.288 --> 33:47.348
Whoa, no, he's not.
I agreed to let you in the house,

33:47.458 --> 33:50.256
- not Doo-Doo over here.
- Doo-Dah.

33:50.361 --> 33:52.693
- Nobody's talkin' to you.
- [Groans] Look.

33:52.797 --> 33:54.560
I'll give you $25,000.

33:56.868 --> 33:58.426
How you doin', Doo-Dah?

33:58.536 --> 34:00.265
You can stay in the living room.

34:00.371 --> 34:02.669
No, Dad, I'm sleeping
in the living room.

34:02.774 --> 34:04.173
Not anymore.

34:04.275 --> 34:06.835
Where am I gonna sleep?

34:06.944 --> 34:08.935
[Dog barking]

34:11.815 --> 34:14.045
Ow.

34:14.152 --> 34:15.983
I hate these people.

34:16.487 --> 34:17.755
<i>[The Waitresses:
Christmas Wrapping]</i>

34:17.755 --> 34:18.652
<i>[The Waitresses:
Christmas Wrapping]</i>

34:30.635 --> 34:33.502
Everybody get some presents,
get your shoppin' done,

34:33.603 --> 34:37.335
and then we'll meet at 4:00
at Santa's Village to take pictures.

34:37.442 --> 34:39.306
Kids, don't lose track of time.

34:39.409 --> 34:41.639
Mom, you wanna stick
with Doo-Dah?

34:41.746 --> 34:45.079
- Why me?
- He's your father.

34:45.183 --> 34:48.208
- [Doo-Dah] How come you never call?
- Tom! Tom! Tom!

34:48.319 --> 34:49.911
Yes, Drew?

34:50.021 --> 34:52.819
Aren't you forgettin' something, T-Bone?

34:54.292 --> 34:57.489
Here you go, Lenny.
Happy holidays to you.

34:57.595 --> 34:59.392
- [Lenny] You too.
- Hey, Tommy!

34:59.497 --> 35:01.488
[Laughing] Nice hat.

35:01.599 --> 35:05.365
- How's the holidays?
- Considering I got a pain in my ass

35:05.470 --> 35:07.495
about six feet tall
in my house, all right.

35:07.605 --> 35:09.095
Oh, relatives, huh?

35:09.207 --> 35:11.198
- Kinda.
- Oh, your wife's family.

35:11.309 --> 35:14.506
They hang around your house
all day and drink your beer.

35:15.413 --> 35:17.438
They eat your salami.

35:18.483 --> 35:22.078
- Hey, guys! Wait up!
- [Alicia sighs]

35:22.186 --> 35:23.653
- [Screeching]
- [Honking]

35:23.754 --> 35:26.348
[Man] Asshole!

35:26.457 --> 35:28.823
<i>[Santa Claus is Comin' to Town]</i>

35:46.210 --> 35:48.440
[Drew] All right, there we go.

35:48.546 --> 35:49.945
Excuse me.

35:53.351 --> 35:55.182
All of you?

35:59.090 --> 36:00.284
Mom, this sucks.

36:00.391 --> 36:02.416
Tell your father.
He made the deal.

36:02.527 --> 36:04.461
Everybody say "Merry Christmas."

36:04.562 --> 36:07.998
- [All] Merry Christmas!
- [Santa and Drew] Ho, ho, ho!

36:11.502 --> 36:13.993
Doo-Dah, interest you
in a Christmas cookie?

36:14.105 --> 36:15.595
I can't. I'm diabetic.

36:15.706 --> 36:17.731
That dog won't hunt, my friend.

36:17.842 --> 36:20.367
Doo-Dah wasn't diabetic.
Go ahead and take one.

36:20.478 --> 36:22.309
Look, kid, I get that.

36:22.413 --> 36:25.211
But if I eat this thing,
I can't act not dead.

36:25.316 --> 36:26.874
- [Tires screeching]
- Hey!

36:26.984 --> 36:28.975
Slow down.
The roads are icy.

36:29.086 --> 36:32.817
- I don't want you to kill your family!
- [Drew] Perfect, Christine.

36:32.924 --> 36:35.358
That's what my mom
would've said. Good improv.

36:35.459 --> 36:38.758
Before your father
threw her out of the car.

36:38.863 --> 36:40.387
[Door squeaks]

36:40.498 --> 36:43.296
Ah, the old carriage house.
Brings back memories.

36:43.401 --> 36:45.335
- What's going on?
- Brian, go inside.

36:45.436 --> 36:47.836
What? Come on! Dad.

36:47.939 --> 36:50.533
I'm in my pajamas.
You want me to sleep outside?

36:50.641 --> 36:51.972
Go.

36:52.877 --> 36:54.811
Fine.

36:55.813 --> 37:00.079
I can't go in my room, I get...
You know, when I become a serial killer

37:00.184 --> 37:01.378
don't act surprised.

37:01.485 --> 37:03.453
Think positive, Bris-eye.

37:03.554 --> 37:06.546
Use your positive mindset.
That's not what we talked about.

37:06.657 --> 37:08.557
It's hard to get through to him.

37:08.659 --> 37:10.456
So what's goin' on?
What's up?

37:10.561 --> 37:12.256
You gotta go.

37:12.363 --> 37:14.695
- What?
- We can't do this no more.

37:16.067 --> 37:17.762
What do you mean?
What can't we do?

37:17.868 --> 37:21.827
Christine and I,
we're thinkin' about breakin' up.

37:23.207 --> 37:26.973
What? Why?
Is it my fault? Something I did?

37:27.078 --> 37:30.070
Is it the hat? Forget it.
Wear whatever you want, Tom.

37:30.181 --> 37:32.274
It's not you.
It's nothin' to do with you.

37:32.383 --> 37:36.683
It's been goin' on for a long time.
We're just... It's not workin' out.

37:36.787 --> 37:40.689
We were gonna wait till after
the holidays to tell the kids,

37:40.791 --> 37:42.486
and you know, with you here,

37:42.593 --> 37:46.256
and with your Christmas cheer crap,
it's making it worse.

