one of those lucid moments.

49:02.205 --> 49:05.038
- I wasn't going for that.
- Okay, I see.

49:05.142 --> 49:07.906
All right, little Miss Grinch.

49:08.011 --> 49:10.571
I know you're a sophisticated,
modern woman

49:10.681 --> 49:14.947
that's very jaded and nothing
gets to you, and you have no emotions.

49:15.052 --> 49:17.020
But I'd be willing to bet
that even you,

49:17.120 --> 49:19.748
before you got old...

49:19.856 --> 49:21.721
...- er than you are now,

49:21.825 --> 49:26.159
but still as young, attractive,
smart and beautiful...

49:26.263 --> 49:28.163
[sniffling] That's better.

49:28.265 --> 49:29.459
I don't know, like,

49:29.566 --> 49:34.128
some moment in your childhood
before everything got complicated,

49:34.237 --> 49:35.465
when you were happy.

49:35.572 --> 49:37.563
You must have some moment in your life

49:37.674 --> 49:40.939
that you'd like to go back and relive.

49:42.846 --> 49:44.541
Yeah.

49:44.648 --> 49:47.583
Once,

49:47.684 --> 49:51.586
I was, like, nine years old

49:51.688 --> 49:55.146
and we had just had
this ice storm.

49:55.258 --> 49:59.126
I was walking home from school
through Bishop Park.

49:59.229 --> 50:02.221
You know that one big oak tree
in the middle?

50:02.332 --> 50:04.732
It was completely frozen.

50:04.835 --> 50:06.962
All the branches were icicles.

50:07.070 --> 50:09.800
It was just...
It was incredible.

50:09.906 --> 50:13.603
It completely stopped me
in my tracks.

50:13.710 --> 50:15.541
I remember standing underneath it

50:15.645 --> 50:20.878
pretending that I was a princess
in a magical crystal palace.

50:20.984 --> 50:22.474
It was really...

50:22.586 --> 50:25.350
It was beautiful.

50:27.190 --> 50:29.283
[Blowing]

50:29.393 --> 50:32.385
